st of vehicles in Marvel Comics#Quinjet|Quinjet]] the New Warriors had originally stolen from the [[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]]. The Folding Circle crashed in [[Madripoor]] and tried to become players in the Madripoor underworld.<ref>Night Thrasher #3-4</ref>\\n\\n===Civil War/The Initiative===\\nDuring the [[Civil War (comics)|Civil War]] event, Smiling Tiger was forced to join the [[Thunderbolts (comics)|Thunderbolts]].<ref>Thunderbolts 103-104, 107</ref>\\n\\nSmiling Tiger has been identified as one of the 142 registered superheroes who appear on the cover of the comic book \'\'[[Avengers: The Initiative]]\'\' #1. <ref>[http://www.marvel.com/news/comicstories.947 Avengers: The Initiative #1 Character Map]</ref>\\n\\n==Universal Wellspring==\\nSmiling Tiger is a [[Mutate (comics)|Mutate]] who like the majority of the [[Folding Circle]] are descended from a cult whose members have tapped into the energy of the Universal Wellspring for centuries.\\n\\n==References==\\n{{reflist}}\\n\\n[[Category:Characters created by Fabian Nicieza]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutates]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\\n\\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}'